[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hospitals in East Midlands collect equipment for Gaza

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Hospitals in the East Midlands are collecting thousands of items of medical equipment to send to war-torn Gaza.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
12 August 2014 Last updated at 21:38 BST
Organisers are appealing for equipment the NHS no longer needs but is in good condition.
BBC reporter Rob Sissons spoke to surgeon Irfan Akhtar and theatre manager Denise Guzdz from Nottinghamshire and consultant Sherif Awad from Derby about the project.
